race.comment: SONDER (4) had a bit on his rivals last time out, scoring an impressive 3 lengths maiden win over 2400m at Bendigo. Looks a horse with a bit of promise over a staying trip and he finds a very winnable affair again. MIGHTY MAC (3) is another off a maiden win, getting the job done at Geelong. He'll be rock hard fit and should measure up well. CUT NO ICE (7) has been in the placings at her last two starts, finishing second last time over 1700m at Gawler. Up in trip now should suit this mare by Reliable Man, expect she goes forward and runs well. STAR TESTYMONY (1) was poor last time at Donald but had been good prior in a better race and can bounce back. REEL BLESSED (5) is mixing form but can sneak into the minor money.
